    ðŸ”¹ `m4 -Dvariable=value file.m4`  --> ðŸ”‘ Defines the variable `variable` with the value `value`. Can be used within the `.m4` file.
    ðŸ”¹ `m4 -Uvariable file.m4`  --> ðŸ—‘ï¸ Undefines the variable `variable`.

ðŸ›  **Examples:**

    $ m4 input.m4

    ðŸ”¹ Preprocesses `input.m4` and prints the result to the terminal.

    $ m4 -o output.txt input.m4

    ðŸ”¹ Preprocesses `input.m4` and saves the result to `output.txt`.

    $ m4 -DVERSION=1.2.3 config.m4 > config.txt

    ðŸ”¹ Defines the `VERSION` variable with the value `1.2.3`, preprocesses `config.m4`, and saves the result to `config.txt`.

